reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A very nice set.
reviews.reviewText: I have only one negative and a suggestion. The neg is it doesn't come with a meat fork. Needs one. And the container to hold the utensils in could be better designed so the the other things like the pizza cutter and measuring spoons (etc) could be at hand rather than having to put them in a drawer. This set is very well made and seems to not leave gouges in my cookware. Best is it won't melt like the plastic set does.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 15, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good variety of tools that food doesn’t stick to.
reviews.reviewText: NUMBER ONE THING: do not use stainless steel with your non stick pots because it will scratch the non stick coating!These work pretty well. Used them with cast iron. There are a few things I didn’t and probably never will use (wine opener.. I just don’t drink wine but the set was a good enough deal that I don’t care about not using one or two things!) but the rest were all pretty good.The cheese grater is a little harder to use just holding, I think I’d prefer a stand one but it worked just fine, just took a little more work.The slotted spoon didn’t let any pasta besides spaghetti through. Great for serving. I do wish a pasta spoon specifically was included in the set.The tongs were easy to maneuver with one hand. I could pull the open tab or push it back in easily and it didn’t get stuck.Pizza cutter did the job. Spatulas were able to flip eggs without the eggs getting stuck. I’ve only had them about a week but these are good tools for a good price (the same things are $8/each at Target). Good gift set for someone for like a wedding or house warming gift because it has everything you need besides the pasta spoon!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice stainless steel set
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a stainless steel set to replace my current collection of various plastic, aluminum, and wooden utensils. This is a nice set that has everything I need. Reasonably priced. The handles are comfortable to hold. I do notice water spots on them after washing, but that's not a big deal to me. I didn't use the holder it came with. The bottom snaps on the holder but I don't think it's very strong. It came apart when I was moving the holder. It snapped right back on - but I didn't trust it anymore so I decided to keep my current holder to use with this set. It would be nice if the holder was one solid piece instead of a bottom piece that snaps on. But overall I am happy with this set.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Poor quality for the price
reviews.reviewText: Good customer service. If you want to press something like a burger the spatula will bend. I just now used the can opener for the first time and noticed rust at the handles.. Just poor quality all around..
